<!-- Q1 -->
<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A parabola is defined by:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">f(x) = −2(x + 3)² + 8</span>
      <div class="hint">Rewrite (x + 3) as (x − (−3)) to identify h = −3. The vertex is (h, k) = (−3, 8). Since a = −2 &lt; 0, the parabola opens down — so k = 8 is a maximum.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Vertex Form</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the <strong>maximum value</strong> of f(x) and at what x does it occur?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>Maximum of 8 at x = 3</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>Maximum of 8 at x = −3</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>Maximum of −3 at x = 8</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>Minimum of 8 at x = −3</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct!</strong> Maximum of 8 at x = −3.<div class="fb-work">f(x) = −2(x+3)² + 8<br>Vertex form: a=−2, h=−3, k=8<br>Vertex: (−3, 8)<br>a = −2 &lt; 0 → parabola opens DOWN → vertex is a MAXIMUM<br>Maximum value = k = 8, occurring at x = h = −3 ✓<br><br>Option A has the wrong sign for x (h = −3, not +3).<br>Option C confuses h and k.<br>Option D says minimum but a&lt;0 means it's a maximum.</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> In f(x) = a(x−h)²+k: vertex = (h, k). Here (x+3) = (x−(−3)), so h = −3. Since a = −2 &lt; 0, the parabola opens down — vertex is a maximum, not minimum. What is k?<div class="fb-work">h = −3, k = 8 → maximum of 8 at x = −3</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q2 -->
<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A parabola in standard form:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">f(x) = x² − 8x + 7</span>
      <div class="hint">Find the axis of symmetry using x = −b/(2a) = −(−8)/(2·1) = 4. Then substitute x = 4 to find the vertex y-value. The vertex is the minimum since a = 1 &gt; 0.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Standard to Vertex</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which is the correct <strong>vertex form</strong> of f(x) = x² − 8x + 7?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>(x − 4)² − 9</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>(x − 4)² + 9</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>(x + 4)² − 9</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>(x − 8)² + 7</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct! (x − 4)² − 9</strong><div class="fb-work">Axis: x = −(−8)/(2·1) = 4<br>f(4) = 16 − 32 + 7 = −9<br>Vertex: (4, −9)<br>Vertex form: (x − 4)² − 9<br>Verify: x²−8x+16−9 = x²−8x+7 ✓<br><br>Option B has wrong sign for k (+9 vs −9).<br>Option C has wrong sign for h (+4 gives h=−4).<br>Option D doesn't follow the vertex form pattern.</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Find axis: x = −b/(2a) = 4. Then f(4) = 16 − 32 + 7 = −9. Vertex is (4, −9) so vertex form is (x − 4)² + (−9).<div class="fb-work">f(x) = (x − 4)² − 9</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q3 -->
<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A ball is thrown upward. Its height h in feet after t seconds is modeled by:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">h(t) = −16t² + 64t + 5</span>
      <div class="hint">The maximum height occurs at the vertex. Find t at the vertex using t = −b/(2a) = −64/(2·(−16)). Then substitute to find the maximum height h.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Real-World Parabola</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the <strong>maximum height</strong> the ball reaches?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>64 feet</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>69 feet</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>5 feet</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>128 feet</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! 69 feet</strong><div class="fb-work">Vertex at t = −64/(2·(−16)) = −64/(−32) = 2 seconds<br>h(2) = −16(4) + 64(2) + 5<br>= −64 + 128 + 5<br>= 69 feet ✓<br><br>Option C (5 feet) is the initial height h(0) — not the maximum.<br>Option A (64) is just the coefficient of t — not a height.<br>Option D overcounts.</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Maximum height is the y-coordinate of the vertex. Find t at vertex: t = −b/(2a) = −64/(2×(−16)) = 2. Then compute h(2).<div class="fb-work">h(2) = −16(4)+64(2)+5 = −64+128+5 = 69 feet</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

