        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! x³ − 2x² + x + 2</strong><div class="fb-work">(2x³ − 4x + 3) − (x³ + 2x² − 5x + 1)<br>= 2x³ − 4x + 3 − x³ − 2x² + 5x − 1<br>Group by degree:<br>x³: 2x³ − x³ = x³<br>x²: 0 − 2x² = −2x²<br>x: −4x + 5x = x<br>const: 3 − 1 = 2<br>= x³ − 2x² + x + 2 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Distribute the negative to ALL terms in the second polynomial: −x³ − 2x² + 5x − 1. Then combine: x³ terms, x² terms, x terms, and constants separately.<div class="fb-work">= x³ − 2x² + x + 2</div></div>
