      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Which is equivalent to x^(3/2)?</div>
      <span class="math-eq">x^(3/2)</span>
      <div class="hint">The exponent 3/2 means: denominator 2 is the root (square root), numerator 3 is the power. So x^(3/2) = (√x)³ = √(x³).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Radical Conversion</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which expression equals x^(3/2)?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1"><div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>∛(x²)</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>√(x³)</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>x·√x · this is same as √(x³)</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>(∛x)²</div></div>
      <div class="q-actions">
