      <span class="math-eq">√(50x⁴y²)</span>
      <div class="hint">Factor the radicand: 50 = 25·2, x⁴ = (x²)², y² = y². Pull out perfect squares: √25 = 5, √(x⁴) = x², √(y²) = |y|. Assume y > 0.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Simplifying Radicals</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which is the simplified form?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2"><div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>5x²y√2</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>5x²√(2y²)</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>25x²y√2</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>5xy√2</div></div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! 5x²y√2</strong><div class='fb-work'>√(50x⁴y²)<br>= √(25·2·x⁴·y²)<br>= √25 · √2 · √(x⁴) · √(y²)<br>= 5 · √2 · x² · y<br>= 5x²y√2 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Factor out all perfect squares: 50 = 25·2, x⁴ = (x²)², y² = y². Take √ of each perfect square separately.<div class='fb-work'>√25·√2·x²·y = 5x²y√2</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
