<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A population of bacteria starts at 400 and doubles every hour.</div>
      <span class="math-eq">P(t) = 400 · 2ᵗ</span>
      <div class="hint">After t hours, the population has doubled t times. Substitute t = 3 directly into the formula.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Exponential Growth</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the population after 3 hours?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0"><div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>2400</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>3200</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>1600</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>6400</div></div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! 3200</strong><div class='fb-work'>P(3) = 400 · 2³ = 400 · 8 = 3200 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Substitute t = 3: P(3) = 400 · 2³. Calculate 2³ first, then multiply by 400.<div class='fb-work'>400 · 8 = 3200</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div><div class="q-panel " id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A car's value depreciates. Its value after t years is:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">V(t) = 24000 · (0.85)ᵗ</span>
      <div class="hint">The base 0.85 = 1 − 0.15, meaning 15% depreciation per year. The initial value is 24000 (when t = 0).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Interpreting Decay</div>
      <div class="q-text">What does the value 0.85 represent in this model?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1"><div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>The car loses $0.85 in value each year</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>The car retains 85% of its value each year</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>The car's value after 85 years</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>The car gains 85% in value each year</div></div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct!</strong> In V(t) = 24000·(0.85)ᵗ, the base 0.85 means each year the car retains 85% of its previous value — equivalently, it loses 15% per year. This is exponential decay with a decay rate of 15%.</div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> In f(x) = a·bˣ, the base b is the multiplier applied each period. b = 0.85 means each year the output is multiplied by 0.85 — the car keeps 85% of its value (losing 15%).<div class='fb-work'>b = 0.85 → retains 85% per year</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div><div class="q-panel " id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Which table represents an exponential function?</div>
      <span class="math-eq">Choose the table where consecutive y-values have a constant ratio.</span>
      <div class="hint">For each table, divide each y-value by the previous one. If the ratio is constant, it's exponential. If the differences are constant, it's linear.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Identifying Exponential</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which (x, y) table shows exponential behavior?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2"><div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>x: 0,1,2,3 · y: 2,4,6,8 (differences = 2)</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>x: 0,1,2,3 · y: 3,9,27,81 (ratios = 3)</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>x: 0,1,2,3 · y: 1,4,9,16 (differences vary)</div><div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>x: 0,1,2,3 · y: 5,10,15,20 (differences = 5)</div></div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct!</strong> Table B has y-values 3, 9, 27, 81. Each is 3 times the previous: 9/3=3, 27/9=3, 81/27=3. Constant ratio = 3 → exponential function f(x) = 3·3ˣ = 3^(x+1). Tables A and D are linear (constant differences). Table C is quadratic.</div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> For each option, compute the ratio of consecutive y-values (divide each by the previous). Exponential: constant ratio. Linear: constant difference.<div class='fb-work'>Table B: 9/3=3, 27/9=3, 81/27=3 → constant ratio ✓</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
