      <div class="problem-text">A swimming pool holds 45,000 liters of water. A pump drains the pool at a rate of 250 liters per minute.</div>
      <div class="hint">Set up: 45,000 liters ÷ (250 liters/minute) = minutes. Then convert minutes to hours by dividing by 60.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Rate Conversion</div>
      <div class="q-text">How many <strong>hours</strong> will it take to drain the pool completely?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
