<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A scientist measures a concentration of 4.5 milligrams per deciliter (mg/dL). She needs to convert this to micrograms per milliliter (μg/mL).</div>
      <div class="problem-text" style="margin-top:0.5rem;font-size:12px;color:#6b7280;">Conversions: 1 mg = 1,000 μg · 1 dL = 100 mL</div>
      <div class="hint">Set up the chain: 4.5 mg/dL × (1,000 μg/mg) × (1 dL/100 mL). Units should cancel to leave μg/mL.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Multi-Unit Conversion</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is 4.5 mg/dL expressed in <strong>μg/mL</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>0.045 μg/mL</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>45 μg/mL</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>450 μg/mL</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>4,500 μg/mL</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! 45 μg/mL</strong><div class="fb-work">4.5 mg/dL × (1,000 μg/mg) × (1 dL/100 mL)<br>= 4.5 × 1,000/100 μg/mL<br>= 4.5 × 10<br>= 45 μg/mL ✓<br><br>Unit check: (mg/dL)(μg/mg)(dL/mL) → mg cancels, dL cancels → μg/mL ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Chain the conversions: 4.5 mg/dL × (1,000 μg/mg) × (1 dL/100 mL). The mg cancels and the dL cancels — what remains is μg/mL.<div class="fb-work">4.5 × 1,000 ÷ 100 = 45 μg/mL</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
