<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A bag contains 4 red marbles, 6 blue marbles, and 2 green marbles. One marble is drawn at random.</div>
      <div class="hint">Total marbles = 4 + 6 + 2 = 12. For P(not green): use the complement — P(not green) = 1 − P(green) = 1 − 2/12.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Basic Probability</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the probability of drawing a marble that is <strong>not green</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>1/6</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>5/6</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>5/12</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>1/2</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! 5/6</strong><div class="fb-work">Total marbles = 12 · Green marbles = 2<br>P(green) = 2/12 = 1/6<br>P(not green) = 1 − 1/6 = 5/6 ✓<br><br>Or directly: non-green = 4+6 = 10<br>P(not green) = 10/12 = 5/6 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> P(not green) = 1 − P(green). There are 2 green marbles out of 12 total.<div class="fb-work">P(green) = 2/12 = 1/6 · P(not green) = 1−1/6 = 5/6</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Use the two-way table:</div>
      <div class="table-wrap" style="margin:0.75rem 0;">
        <table class="two-way" style="font-size:12px;">
          <tr><th></th><th>Passed</th><th>Failed</th><th>Total</th></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Studied</strong></td><td>56</td><td>14</td><td class="total">70</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>Didn't study</strong></td><td>12</td><td>18</td><td class="total">30</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="total">Total</td><td class="total">68</td><td class="total">32</td><td class="total">100</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="hint">Conditional probability: P(passed | studied) means "given that the student studied, what fraction passed?" Use the Studied row total (70) as the denominator — not the grand total of 100.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Conditional Probability</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the probability that a student <strong>passed, given they studied</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>56/100</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>56/68</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>56/70</div>
