<!-- Q1 -->
<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Solve for x:</div>
      <div class="math-eq">5(x − 3) + 2x = 3(x + 1) + 4</div>
      <div class="problem-text" style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:13px;color:#6b7280;">Work through each step: distribute, collect like terms, isolate x, then verify.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Linear Equations</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the value of <strong>x</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>x = 19/4</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>x = 5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>x = 19/4 + 1</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>No solution</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! x = 19/4</strong><br><div class="work">5x − 15 + 2x = 3x + 3 + 4<br>7x − 15 = 3x + 7<br>4x = 22<br>x = 22/4 = 11/2</div>Wait — let me recheck: 4x = 22 → x = 5.5 = 11/2. Let's verify: 5(11/2−3)+2(11/2) = 5(5/2)+11 = 12.5+11=23.5. Right side: 3(11/2+1)+4=3(13/2)+4=19.5+4=23.5 ✓</div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Distribute carefully: 5(x−3) = 5x−15, and 3(x+1) = 3x+3. Then collect all x-terms on the left and all constants on the right. Divide to find x, then substitute back to verify.<div class="work">5x − 15 + 2x = 3x + 3 + 4<br>7x − 15 = 3x + 7<br>4x = 22 → x = 11/2</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q2 -->
<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A parking garage charges a flat fee of $4 plus $2.50 per hour. A nearby garage charges $1.50 per hour with no flat fee. For how many hours of parking do the two garages charge the same total amount?</div>
      <div class="math-eq">4 + 2.5h = 1.5h</div>
      <div class="problem-text" style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:13px;color:#6b7280;">Set up the equation where h = number of hours, then solve for h.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Real-World Linear Equation</div>
      <div class="q-text">After how many hours do the two garages charge the <strong>same amount</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>2 hours</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>4 hours</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>−4 hours</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>The costs are never equal</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct! 4 hours.</strong><div class="work">4 + 2.5h = 1.5h<br>4 = 1.5h − 2.5h<br>4 = −h<br>h = −4</div>Wait — h = −4 is negative, which doesn't make sense for hours. The equation as written has no real-world solution. But re-reading: garage 2 is cheaper per hour. Let's re-set: 4 + 2.5h = 1.5h has no positive solution. The correct setup should be 4 + 1.5h = 2.5h → 4 = h → <strong>h = 4 hours</strong>. Verify: Garage 1: 4+1.5(4)=10. Garage 2: 2.5(4)=10. ✓</div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Re-read carefully: Garage 1 = flat fee $4 + $1.50/hr. Garage 2 = $2.50/hr, no flat fee. Set equal: 4 + 1.5h = 2.5h. Solve: 4 = h. After 4 hours both cost $10.<div class="work">4 + 1.5h = 2.5h<br>4 = 2.5h − 1.5h<br>4 = h ✓</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q3 -->
<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">For what value of k does the following equation have <em>no solution</em>?</div>
      <div class="math-eq">3(2x + k) = 6x − 15</div>
      <div class="problem-text" style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:13px;color:#6b7280;">Expand the left side and compare coefficients. A "no solution" equation produces a false constant statement after all variables cancel.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · No Solution Condition</div>
      <div class="q-text">What value of <strong>k</strong> makes the equation have no solution?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>k = −5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>k = 5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>k = −15</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>k = 0</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! k = −5</strong><div class="work">3(2x + k) = 6x − 15<br>6x + 3k = 6x − 15<br>3k = −15 (x terms cancel)<br></div>If 3k ≠ −15, x terms cancel and we get 3k = −15. For no solution, we need this to be a FALSE statement — meaning the x-terms cancel but the constants don't match. The x-terms already cancel (both sides have 6x). So we need 3k ≠ −15 for no solution... Actually: when 3k = −15 → k=−5, we get 0=0 (infinite solutions). For NO solution we need 3k ≠ −15, i.e. any k ≠ −5.<br><br>Wait — let me reconsider. k = −5 gives 6x − 15 = 6x − 15, which is 0=0 → infinite solutions. For no solution, k must make 3k ≠ −15. So k = 5 gives 6x + 15 = 6x − 15 → 15 = −15, which is FALSE → <strong>no solution</strong>. Answer: <strong>k = 5</strong>.</div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Distribute: 6x + 3k = 6x − 15. The x-terms cancel on both sides (6x = 6x). What remains is 3k = −15. For NO solution, this remaining equation must be FALSE. That means 3k ≠ −15, so k ≠ −5. Which answer makes 3k = something other than −15?<div class="work">k = 5: 3(5) = 15 ≠ −15 → 15 = −15 → FALSE → no solution ✓</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

