<!-- Q1 -->
<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A line passes through the points (−1, 3) and (3, 11).</div>
      <div class="problem-text" style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:12px;color:#6b7280;">Find the slope first using the two points, then substitute one point into y = mx + b to find the y-intercept.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Slope-Intercept Form</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which equation correctly describes the line through (−1, 3) and (3, 11)?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>y = 2x + 5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>y = 3x + 6</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>y = 2x − 5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>y = 4x + 7</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! y = 2x + 5</strong><div class="fb-work">m = (11 − 3) / (3 − (−1)) = 8 / 4 = 2<br>Using (−1, 3): 3 = 2(−1) + b → b = 5<br>y = 2x + 5<br>Check (3, 11): 2(3) + 5 = 11 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Start by finding slope: m = (y₂ − y₁)/(x₂ − x₁) = (11 − 3)/(3 − (−1)). Then substitute one point into y = mx + b to solve for b.<div class="fb-work">m = 8/4 = 2 · Then: 3 = 2(−1) + b → b = 5<br>Answer: y = 2x + 5</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
