      <div class="math-eq">V = 400 − 25t</div>
      <div class="problem-text" style="margin-top:0.6rem;font-size:12px;color:#6b7280;">where V = volume (gallons) and t = time (hours). Answer the question about this linear model.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Interpreting Linear Models</div>
      <div class="q-text">In the equation V = 400 − 25t, what does the value <strong>400</strong> represent?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>The rate at which water drains per hour</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>The number of hours until the tank is empty</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>The initial volume of water in the tank when t = 0</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>The total volume of water drained after 400 hours</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
