<!-- Q1 -->
<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">System of equations</div>
      <span class="math-eq">2x + 3y = 12</span>
      <span class="math-eq">4x − 3y = 6</span>
      <div class="problem-text" style="margin-top:0.75rem; font-size:12px; color:#6b7280;">The y-coefficients are already opposites (+3 and −3). Use elimination — add the equations directly to eliminate y, then solve for x.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Elimination Method</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the solution (x, y) to this system?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>(3, 2)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>(2, 3)</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>(1, 10/3)</div>
