      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! (3, 2)</strong><div class="fb-work">Add: (2x + 3y) + (4x − 3y) = 12 + 6<br>6x = 18 → x = 3<br>Sub into eq 1: 2(3) + 3y = 12<br>6 + 3y = 12 → y = 2<br>Check eq 2: 4(3) − 3(2) = 12 − 6 = 6 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Notice the y-terms are +3y and −3y — they're already set up for elimination! Add the two equations directly. The y's cancel, giving you 6x = 18. Solve for x, then substitute back to find y.<div class="fb-work">Add equations → 6x = 18 → x = 3<br>2(3) + 3y = 12 → y = 2 → (3, 2)</div></div>
