      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Solve the inequality:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">−4x + 3 &gt; 2x − 9</span>
      <div class="problem-text" style="margin-top:0.75rem; font-size:12px; color:#6b7280;">Collect x-terms on one side. Watch carefully: does dividing to isolate x require dividing by a negative? If so, flip the sign.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Solving Inequalities</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which correctly describes all values of x that satisfy the inequality?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>x &gt; 2</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>x &lt; 2</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>x &gt; −2</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>x &lt; −2</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! x &lt; 2</strong><div class="fb-work">−4x + 3 &gt; 2x − 9<br>3 + 9 &gt; 2x + 4x<br>12 &gt; 6x<br>2 &gt; x → x &lt; 2<br>Check: x = 0: −4(0)+3=3 &gt; 2(0)−9=−9 ✓<br>Check: x = 3: −9 &gt; −3? No ✓ (not in solution)</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Move all x-terms to the right and constants to the left, then divide. Alternatively, add 4x to both sides and add 9 to both sides first.<div class="fb-work">−4x + 3 &gt; 2x − 9<br>12 &gt; 6x → x &lt; 2</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
