</div>

<!-- Q1 -->
<div class="q-panel active" id="qp-0">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Solve the absolute value equation:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">|2x − 5| = 11</span>
      <div class="hint">Split into two cases: 2x − 5 = 11 and 2x − 5 = −11. Solve each. Both solutions are valid — check them in the original equation.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Absolute Value Equation</div>
      <div class="q-text">What are all values of <strong>x</strong> that satisfy the equation?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>x = 8 only</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>x = 8 or x = −3</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>x = 3 or x = −8</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>No solution</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! x = 8 or x = −3</strong><div class="fb-work">Case 1: 2x − 5 = 11 → 2x = 16 → x = 8<br>Case 2: 2x − 5 = −11 → 2x = −6 → x = −3<br>Check x=8: |16−5| = |11| = 11 ✓<br>Check x=−3: |−6−5| = |−11| = 11 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Remember absolute value equations always have two cases. Set the inside equal to +11 AND equal to −11. Solve both equations separately.<div class="fb-work">2x − 5 = 11 → x = 8<br>2x − 5 = −11 → x = −3</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q2 -->
<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Solve the absolute value inequality:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">|x + 4| ≤ 7</span>
      <div class="hint">Less than (or equal) → "AND" case → write as a compound inequality: −7 ≤ x + 4 ≤ 7, then subtract 4 from all three parts.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Absolute Value Inequality (&lt;)</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which describes all values of <strong>x</strong> that satisfy the inequality?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>x ≤ 3 or x ≥ −11</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>−3 ≤ x ≤ 11</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>−11 ≤ x ≤ 3</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>x ≤ −11 or x ≥ 3</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct! −11 ≤ x ≤ 3</strong><div class="fb-work">|x + 4| ≤ 7 → −7 ≤ x + 4 ≤ 7<br>Subtract 4: −11 ≤ x ≤ 3<br>Check x=0: |0+4|=4 ≤ 7 ✓ (inside)<br>Check x=−11: |−11+4|=7 ≤ 7 ✓ (boundary)<br>Check x=5: |5+4|=9 ≤ 7 ✗ (correctly excluded)</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> "Less than or equal" → AND → compact interval. Write −7 ≤ x + 4 ≤ 7 and subtract 4 from all three parts.<div class="fb-work">−7 − 4 ≤ x ≤ 7 − 4<br>−11 ≤ x ≤ 3</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'C')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
