      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">A machine is calibrated to fill bottles with exactly 500 ml. Due to mechanical variation, the actual fill amount f can differ from 500 ml by at most 8 ml.</div>
      <span class="math-eq">|f − 500| ≤ 8</span>
      <div class="hint">This models the acceptable range. Solve the inequality to find the minimum and maximum acceptable fill amounts.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Real-World Absolute Value</div>
      <div class="q-text">Which describes the <strong>acceptable range</strong> of fill amounts f?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>f ≤ 492 or f ≥ 508</div>
