      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">If x = −4, evaluate the expression:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">|3x + 2| − |x − 1|</span>
      <div class="hint">Substitute x = −4 into each absolute value separately. Calculate what's inside each |bar|, then take the absolute value, then subtract.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Evaluating Expressions</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the value of the expression when <strong>x = −4</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>−15</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>15</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>−5</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! 5</strong><div class="fb-work">|3(−4) + 2| − |(−4) − 1|<br>= |−12 + 2| − |−5|<br>= |−10| − |−5|<br>= 10 − 5<br>= 5 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Substitute x = −4 carefully into each part. Calculate inside the bars first: 3(−4)+2 = −10, and (−4)−1 = −5. Then take absolute values of each: |−10| = 10, |−5| = 5. Finally subtract.<div class="fb-work">10 − 5 = 5</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'B')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
