</div>

<!-- Q2 -->
<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Given that |2x − 6| = 10, find all possible values of x², then determine which value of x² is larger.</div>
      <span class="math-eq">|2x − 6| = 10</span>
      <div class="hint">First solve for x (two cases). Then square each solution. The SAT often asks for x² or |x| after solving an absolute value equation — don't stop at x.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Multi-Step Absolute Value</div>
      <div class="q-text">What is the <strong>sum</strong> of all possible values of x?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>6</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>8</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>−2</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>4</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct! Sum = 6</strong><div class="fb-work">|2x − 6| = 10<br>Case 1: 2x − 6 = 10 → 2x = 16 → x = 8<br>Case 2: 2x − 6 = −10 → 2x = −4 → x = −2<br>Sum of solutions: 8 + (−2) = 6 ✓<br><br>Note: For any |ax + b| = c, the sum of solutions always equals −b/a. Here: −(−6)/2 = 3... wait, the midpoint is 3 and solutions are 3±5, so 8 and −2, sum = 6 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Solve both cases: 2x − 6 = 10 gives one solution, and 2x − 6 = −10 gives the other. Add the two solutions together.<div class="fb-work">x = 8 and x = −2<br>Sum: 8 + (−2) = 6</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q3 -->
<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">On a number line, point A is at position −3 and point B is at position 7. Point P is at position x.</div>
      <div class="problem-text" style="margin-top:0.6rem;">The condition that P is closer to A than to B can be written as:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">|x − (−3)| &lt; |x − 7|</span>
      <div class="hint">Use the distance interpretation: |x + 3| is P's distance from A, and |x − 7| is P's distance from B. Square both sides to remove the absolute values, then solve the resulting inequality.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Distance & Absolute Value</div>
      <div class="q-text">For which values of x is point P <strong>closer to A than to B</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>x &lt; 2</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>x &gt; 2</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>x &lt; 5</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>−3 &lt; x &lt; 7</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! x &lt; 2</strong><div class="fb-work">The midpoint between −3 and 7 is (−3+7)/2 = 2.<br>P is closer to A when x is to the left of the midpoint: x &lt; 2.<br><br>Algebraically: |x+3| &lt; |x−7|<br>Square both sides: (x+3)² &lt; (x−7)²<br>x²+6x+9 &lt; x²−14x+49<br>20x &lt; 40 → x &lt; 2 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> The midpoint between −3 and 7 is 2. Points to the left of 2 are closer to A (at −3), and points to the right are closer to B (at 7). Which inequality captures "to the left of the midpoint"?<div class="fb-work">Midpoint = (−3+7)/2 = 2<br>Closer to A: x &lt; 2</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
