      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Solve by factoring:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">x² − 7x + 12 = 0</span>
      <div class="hint">Find two numbers that multiply to 12 and add to −7. Both numbers must be negative since their sum is negative and product is positive. Then write as (x + p)(x + q) = 0.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 1 · Factoring</div>
      <div class="q-text">What are the solutions to the equation?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-0">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>x = 3 and x = 4</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>x = −3 and x = −4</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>x = 3 and x = −4</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(0,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>x = 1 and x = 12</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-ok"><strong>Correct! x = 3 and x = 4</strong><div class="fb-work">Need p × q = 12 and p + q = −7<br>Try: −3 × −4 = 12 ✓ and −3 + (−4) = −7 ✓<br>(x − 3)(x − 4) = 0<br>x = 3 or x = 4<br>Check: 9 − 21 + 12 = 0 ✓ and 16 − 28 + 12 = 0 ✓</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-0-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Find two numbers that multiply to +12 and add to −7. Since the sum is negative and product is positive, both numbers must be negative.<div class="fb-work">−3 × −4 = 12 and −3 + (−4) = −7<br>(x−3)(x−4) = 0 → x = 3 or x = 4</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-0" onclick="check(0,'A')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q2 -->
<div class="q-panel" id="qp-1">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">Use the quadratic formula to solve:</div>
      <span class="math-eq">3x² + 4x − 2 = 0</span>
      <div class="hint">Identify a = 3, b = 4, c = −2. Compute the discriminant: b² − 4ac = 16 + 24 = 40. Then x = (−4 ± √40) / 6. Simplify √40 = 2√10.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 2 · Quadratic Formula</div>
      <div class="q-text">What are the solutions to 3x² + 4x − 2 = 0?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-1">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>x = (−4 ± √40) / 3</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>x = (4 ± √40) / 6</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>x = (−4 ± √40) / 6</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(1,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>x = (−4 ± √56) / 6</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-ok"><strong>Correct!</strong><div class="fb-work">a=3, b=4, c=−2<br>x = (−4 ± √(16+24)) / (2·3)<br>= (−4 ± √40) / 6<br>= (−4 ± 2√10) / 6<br>= (−2 ± √10) / 3<br><br>Option A divides by 3 (should be 2a=6).<br>Option B uses +4 instead of −b=−4.<br>Option D uses wrong discriminant: 16−4(3)(−2)=16+24=40 not 56.</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-1-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> Apply x = (−b ± √(b²−4ac)) / (2a) carefully. With a=3, b=4, c=−2: the denominator is 2a = 6, not 3. And −b = −4.<div class="fb-work">x = (−4 ± √(16+24)) / 6 = (−4 ± √40) / 6</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-1" onclick="check(1,'C')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Q3 -->
<div class="q-panel" id="qp-2">
  <div class="math-layout">
    <div class="problem-panel">
      <div class="panel-label">Problem</div>
      <div class="problem-text">The equation x² + kx + 16 = 0 has exactly one real solution.</div>
      <div class="hint">Exactly one real solution means the discriminant = 0. Set b² − 4ac = 0 and solve for k. Remember k can be positive or negative.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-panel-inner">
      <div class="q-label">Question 3 · Discriminant</div>
      <div class="q-text">What are the possible values of <strong>k</strong>?</div>
      <div class="opts" id="opts-2">
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'A')"><span class="opt-l">A</span>k = 4 only</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'B')"><span class="opt-l">B</span>k = 8 only</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'C')"><span class="opt-l">C</span>k = 8 or k = −8</div>
        <div class="opt" onclick="pick(2,this,'D')"><span class="opt-l">D</span>k = 4 or k = −4</div>
      </div>
      <div class="q-actions">
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-ok"><strong>Correct! k = 8 or k = −8</strong><div class="fb-work">Exactly one solution → discriminant = 0<br>b² − 4ac = 0<br>k² − 4(1)(16) = 0<br>k² − 64 = 0<br>k² = 64<br>k = ±8<br><br>Check k=8: x²+8x+16=(x+4)²=0 → x=−4 ✓ (one solution)<br>Check k=−8: x²−8x+16=(x−4)²=0 → x=4 ✓ (one solution)</div></div>
        <div class="feedback" id="fb-2-fail"><strong>Not quite.</strong> One real solution means discriminant = 0. Set k² − 4(1)(16) = 0 and solve for k. Don't forget k can be positive or negative — both give exactly one solution.<div class="fb-work">k² = 64 → k = ±8</div></div>
        <button class="btn-check" id="btn-2" onclick="check(2,'C')" disabled>Check answer</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

